The puprose of this project is to provide the animal shelter with a low cost, automatic food dispenser to feed pets at schedule times and alert staff when they are not eating.
It is assumed that the dispenser has limited storage, limited memory and processing power, feeds one pet at a time with one type of pet food, all serving sizes are equal, feeding times are set, and staff are available to respond to alerts. 
Inputs and Outputs include a Clock, Feeding Schedule, Food Level Sensor, bowl weight sensor, Servo Motor activation to dispense the food, and Alert Notification to notify staff if the pet is not eating.
